comments.body:
I would split the functionality. There are too many scenarion and it is imposibble to fit them all into single control.
<br>To me the CanvasView looks a lot like some kind of MapControl.. You have some background and bunch of items placed in X and Y coordinates, that are selectable.
<br>Drag and Drop is separate concern. What about this:
<br>&lt;CanvasView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}" 
<br>LeftPath="X" 
<br>RightPath="Y"&gt; 
<br>&lt;CanvasView.ItemTemplate&gt; 
<br>&lt;DataTemplate&gt; 
<br>&lt;ManipulationHelper ManipulationCompleted="Item_ManipulationCompleted"&gt; 
<br>   &lt;Rectangle Fill="Red" /&gt;
<br>&lt;/ManipulationHelper&gt; 
<br>&lt;/DataTemplate&gt; 
<br>&lt;CanvasView.ItemTemplate&gt; 
<br>&lt;/CanvasView&gt;
<br>private void Item_ManipulationCompleted(object sender, ManipulationCompletedRoutedEventArgs e) 
<br>{ 
<br>var itemContainer = (FrameworkElement)sender; 
<br>var item = (MyItemViewModel)itemContainer.DataContext; 
<br>item.X += e.Cumulative.Translation.X; 
<br>item.Y += e.Cumulative.Translation.Y; 
<br>}
